🌸 A Woman Who Made an Impact on My Career | #IWD26
The woman who has shaped my confidence, curiosity, and way of thinking is my mom. 💖
She introduced me to art 🎨 and encouraged me to express myself freely. From a young age, she always 
told me to be confident, independent, and never be afraid to explore the world. 🌍

She would always say:
✨ “Do what you like. Explore the world. Stand for yourself and express your thoughts.”

But the most powerful lesson she gave me was about thinking for myself.

One day she told me something I will never forget:
🧠 “You haven’t pawned your brain anywhere, so use it. Don’t blindly believe what others say.”

That simple sentence taught me to question things, think independently, and trust my own mind.
Because of her, I learned to explore, create, and stand strong with my own thoughts. 🌱

💫 Thank you, Mom, for teaching me confidence, independence, and the courage to think freely.
